  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scoping Study Circular Economy Vietnam (Part 2)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Vietnam is one of the world&#x2019;s most vulnerable countries to climate change, with adaptation challenges accordingly severe, especially in the Mekong Delta. Despite of a relatively high rate of (informal) solid urban waste recycling, the current economy leads to the depletion of precious resources and does not account for negative externalities exerted upon the environment. A circular economy presents a sustainable solution to part of the socio-economic and environmental challenges resulting from the current linear economic model in Vietnam. Moreover, Organizations like the governmental CIEM and the VCCI are interested in the potential of circular economy strategies.A scoping study was commissioned by RVO and executed at the end 2017/early 2018 to identify potential areas of circular (business) cooperation between Vietnam and NL. As a result, next steps are needed to bring the concept of circular economy further.This project will result in a local in-depth study giving a clear overview of policy for and actors in the circular economy in Vietnam in order to identify suitable interventions and potential partners. Next to this, a proposal for a high-level round table meeting will be developed and support will be given to organise the meeting. Armed with this information, a Dutch expert will take over the lead at the meeting and will introduce the Dutch circular economy policy, advise on how to set up a Holland Circular Hotspot model and showcase relevant Dutch best practice companies on circular economy, plastics and waste. As a result, an MoU will be signed to prepare the establishment of a private public platform in Vietnam.</narrative>
  </description>
